<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-03-15T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-03-15T19:00:00-05:00" n="981" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d981">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">852.75 National Telephone Co./323:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-15T19:00:00-05:00">March
                                        15, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>31. Your 48, March 14, 4 p.m. We are at a loss to understand this
                                change in attitude on the part of the Spanish Government. We feel
                                that it is high time that the Spanish Government acquiesce in a fair
                                and reasonable settlement of this matter and we are confident that
                                you will continue your efforts to that end.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>